      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ أَشَلِّ الْيَدِ الْيُمْنَى أَوْ أَشَلِّ الْيَدِ الشِّمَالِ سَرَقَ قَالَ تُقْطَعُ يَدُهُ الْيُمْنَى عَلَى كُلِّ حَالٍ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Ibn Mahboub, from Abdullah Bin Sinan, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> regarding a man with a crippled right hand, or a crippled left hand, steals’. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘His right hand would be cut upon every state’."
        ]
      }
